events.originalText: Arab Spring: The Yemeni Revolution began as more than 16,000 protesters demonstrated in Sanaa to demand governmental changes.
events.subtitle: Arab Spring
events.headline: Yemeni Revolution Begins with 16,000 Protesters in Sanaa

events.originalText: Astronomers documented H1504+65, a white dwarf in Ursa Minor with the hottest surface temperature known at the time, at 200,000 kelvins (360,000 °F).
events.subtitle: H1504+65
events.headline: Astronomers Discover White Dwarf with Record-High Temperature

events.originalText: Porfirio Lobo Sosa became the new president of Honduras, ending a constitutional crisis that had begun in 2009 when Manuel Zelaya was forcibly removed from office.
events.subtitle: Porfirio Lobo Sosa
events.headline: Porfirio Lobo Sosa Sworn in as President of Honduras

events.originalText: The first selections for the United States National Recording Registry were announced by the Library of Congress.
events.subtitle: National Recording Registry
events.headline: Library of Congress Announces First Selections for National Recording Registry

events.originalText: Mahamane Ousmane (pictured), the first democratically elected president of Niger, was deposed by Colonel Ibrahim Baré Maïnassara in a military coup d'état.
events.subtitle: Mahamane Ousmane
events.headline: Niger's First Democratically Elected President Ousted in Coup

events.originalText: Six American diplomats who had evaded capture in the Iran hostage crisis escaped with the help of Canadian government officials to Zürich, Switzerland.
events.subtitle: Iran hostage crisis
events.headline: American Diplomats Escape Iran Hostage Crisis to Switzerland

events.originalText: Brisbane, Australia, was flooded when the Brisbane River broke its banks.
events.subtitle: Brisbane
events.headline: Brisbane, Australia, Flooded as Brisbane River Overflows

events.originalText: A fire during a launch simulation for the Apollo 1 mission at Cape Kennedy killed astronauts Gus Grissom, Ed White and Roger Chaffee.
events.subtitle: Apollo 1
events.headline: Tragedy Strikes Apollo 1 Mission Launch Simulation

events.originalText: South Vietnamese prime minister Trần Văn Hương was removed by the military junta of Nguyễn Khánh.
events.subtitle: Trần Văn Hương
events.headline: South Vietnamese Prime Minister Removed by Military Junta

events.originalText: The Soviet Red Army liberated about 7,000 prisoners left behind by the Nazis in Auschwitz concentration camp (entrance pictured).
events.subtitle: Red Army
events.headline: Soviet Red Army Liberates Prisoners at Auschwitz Concentration Camp

events.originalText: A contaminated diphtheria vaccine was used in an Australian immunisation program, leading to the deaths of twelve children and the suspension of immunisation programs in several countries.
events.subtitle: Bundaberg tragedy
events.headline: Contaminated Vaccine Leads to Deaths of Twelve Children

events.originalText: A Russian expedition led by the naval officers Fabian Gottlieb von Bellingshausen and Mikhail Lazarev made the first sighting of the coast of Antarctica.
events.subtitle: First Russian Antarctic Expedition
events.headline: Russian Expedition Makes First Sighting of Antarctica Coast

events.originalText: French Revolutionary Wars: In the Macau Incident, French and Spanish warships encountered a British Royal Navy escort squadron in the Wanshan Archipelago; subsequent events, including which side retreated, were disputed by the commanders present.
events.subtitle: French Revolutionary Wars
events.headline: French and Spanish Warships Encounter British Royal Navy in Macau Incident

events.originalText: The University of Georgia, one of the oldest public universities in the United States, was founded.
events.subtitle: University of Georgia
events.headline: University of Georgia Founded as One of Oldest Public Universities in US

events.originalText: Clement VI issued the papal bull Unigenitus, justifying the power of the pope and the use of indulgences.
events.subtitle: Pope Clement VI
events.headline: Papal Bull Unigenitus Issued by Clement VI

events.originalText: The brothers Stephen and Constantine Lekapenos, having deposed their father as Byzantine emperor a few weeks earlier, were themselves overthrown by Constantine VII, their co-emperor.
events.subtitle: Stephen Lekapenos
events.headline: Constantine VII Overthrows Brothers Stephen and Constantine Lekapenos

events.originalText: Trajan succeeded his adoptive father Nerva as Roman emperor; the Roman Empire reached its maximum extent under his rule.
events.subtitle: AD 98
events.headline: Trajan Succeeds Nerva as Roman Emperor, Empire Reaches Maximum Extent
